## 📦 Standard JSON Response Format

```json
// Success
{ "success": true, "message": "...", "count": N, "total": N, "data": [...] }

// Error
{ "success": false, "message": "...", "errors": { "field": "reason" } }
```

### HTTP Status Codes Used
| Code | Meaning |
|---|---|
| `200` | OK |
| `201` | Created |
| `400` | Bad request |
| `404` | Not found |
| `409` | Duplicate (slug conflict) |
| `422` | Validation failed (with field errors) |
| `500` | Server error |
